<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.187097>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. External and internal morphology of Leucosolenia australis; A—Fixed specimen; B—Tangential view of tube wall; C—Detail showing the apical actine of tetractines penetrating into the lumen; D—Microdiactine with detail of the two tips; E—Diactine; F—Triactine (black arrow) and tetractine (white arrow)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187097/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.187100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Specimens in situ: A— Clathrina fjordica sp. nov.; B— Guancha ramosa sp. nov.; C— Leucaltis nuda sp. nov.; D— Leucosolenia australis; E— Sycon huinayense sp. nov.; F— Sycettusa chilensis sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.187098>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7 A – I. External and internal morphology of Sycon huinayense sp. nov. A—Fixed specimen; B—Detail of the oscular skeleton; C—Transversal section; D—Detail of the distal cone; E—Detail of the tubar skeleton; F—Subatrial (arrow shows a subatrial triactine) and atrial skeletons (at: atrium); G— Diactine I; H—Diactine II; I – Triactine of the cone." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/187098/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

